carbon capture and storage (BECCS), and mineral carbonation. The assistant provides insights into the latest progress, current application status, prevailing challenges, and emerging trends related to these technologies.\n\n### Overall Conclusion\nThese three specialized AI research assistants collectively cover critical pillars of sustainable technology—renewable energy generation, electrified transportation, and carbon management—each providing targeted, real-time intelligence through advanced search and analytical capabilities."]
